-- China to Extend Rare-Earth Stockpiles Nationwide After Test, Nikkei Says
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2010-10-28T20:00:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-28/china-to-extend-rare-earth-stockpiles-nationwide-after-test-nikkei-says.html
China may introduce a stockpiling
system for rare-earth metals nationwide after a successful test
by  Inner Mongolia Baotou Steel Rare-Earth Hi-Tech Co ., Nikkei
English News said, citing people close to the Ministry of Land
and Resources.  Accumulating reserves has made prices easier to maintain
through control of supply, the newspaper reported today. The
company plans to invest 2 billion yuan to 3 billion yuan over
five years to accumulate reserves in 10 locations, the Nikkei
said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  